The paper deals with stability in multi-hop wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses transmission policies and scheduling policies, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of hearing control mechanisms to coordinate transmissions is a topic that falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a new definition of universal stability, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.MA).
